-----------------------------------------------
keywords

------------python literals-----------------------
*-string literal -single line string eg h="hello"
                -multi line string  eg a="hello
                                          world"
                                       b="hello \ world"
                                    eg c='''hello
                                          world'''
*-numeric literal  -int     eg: 23
                  -float   eg: 34.34
                  -complex eg: 3+34j
                  -number type
         decimal       eg num=2
         binary       bin()
         hexadecimal  hex()
         octadecimal  oct()
*-boolean literal
*-special literal   -python contains one special litral called None eg: x
                                                                     print(x)
                                                                     None
-litral collection -4 types
                    tuple, set ,list ,disnary  

